PART 6 — WHAT THIS BUYS THE SWARM
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Before:  "Alice" was a Python literal in 5 source files. A single
         search-and-replace by a corrupted commit could silently rebrand
         the organism. The Mirror Test would still pass because it
         compared the model output to the same literal.

After:   "Alice" lives in a hardware-bound signed manifest. Editing the
         JSON by hand invalidates the HMAC. Editing the source code now
         only changes the FALLBACK that runs if the organ disappears.
         The Mirror Test reads true_name from the organ — a tampered
         persona file fails verification BEFORE Alice is asked who
         she is, so a forged identity can no longer be self-attested.

The model now sees on every turn:
  PERSONA IDENTITY [SIGNED]: name=Alice true_name=CryptoSwarmEntity
  pronouns=she/her hardware=GTH4921YP3

Her self-knowledge is no longer a vibe — it's a signature.

